      "Text": "mongo-c-driver security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mongo-c-driver is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "mongo-c-driver is a project that includes two libraries: libmongoc, a client library written in C for MongoDB. libbson, a library providing useful routines related to building, parsing, and iterating BSON documents.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA compromised third party cloud server or man-in-the-middle attacker could send a malformed HTTP response and cause a crash in applications using the MongoDB C driver.(CVE-2026-4359)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for mongo-c-driver is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "mongo-c-driver",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
